      "text": "<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">A 35-year-old man has been observing a fast as part of a cultural festival for several days. Despite significantly reduced food intake, he surprisingly reports feeling mentally alert and does not experience any dizziness or significant discomfort typically associated with low blood sugar levels. Intrigued by this adaptation, he visits a healthcare provider for a routine check-up. The provider explains how the body adapts to prolonged fasting by utilizing alternative energy sources to maintain brain function and overall metabolism:</span></span></span></p>",
