          "text": "<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Triglyceride breakdown</span></span></span></p>"
        }
      ],
      "text": "<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">A 10-year-old girl presents to the emergency department with severe polyuria and polydipsia. Laboratory tests reveal the presence of ketones in her urine. Considering the metabolic conditions, which is the most likely source of these ketones?</span></span></span></p>",
